Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: AI-Driven Memory Tuning Module

Provides AI/ML-based tuning and optimization for memory allocators and garbage collectors.

Features:
- Workload analysis and profiling
- Auto-configuration of allocators and GC
- Adaptive optimization based on real-time usage
- Integration with memory profiling and stats
- AI/agent-friendly tuning APIs
- Production-ready, robust, and extensible
:End Note


Import "../utilities/common" as Common
Note: AI Tuning Types and Interfaces
Type called "AITuner":
    analyze_workload as Function that takes stats as MemoryStats returns WorkloadProfile
    auto_configure_allocator as Function that takes profile as WorkloadProfile returns AllocatorConfig
    auto_configure_gc as Function that takes profile as WorkloadProfile returns GCConfig
    adaptive_optimize as Function that takes stats as MemoryStats returns OptimizationAction
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "WorkloadProfile":
    workload_type as String
    allocation_pattern as String
    gc_pressure as Float
    fragmentation as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "OptimizationAction":
    action_type as String
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core AI Tuning Functions
Process called "analyze_workload" that takes tuner as AITuner and stats as MemoryStats returns WorkloadProfile:
    Note: Analyzes memory stats to produce a workload profile
    Return WorkloadProfile with:
        workload_type as computed
        allocation_pattern as computed
        gc_pressure as computed
        fragmentation as computed
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "auto_configure_allocator" that takes tuner as AITuner and profile as WorkloadProfile returns AllocatorConfig:
    Note: Auto-configures allocator based on workload
    Return AllocatorConfig

Process called "auto_configure_gc" that takes tuner as AITuner and profile as WorkloadProfile returns GCConfig:
    Note: Auto-configures GC based on workload
    Return GCConfig

Process called "adaptive_optimize" that takes tuner as AITuner and stats as MemoryStats returns OptimizationAction:
    Note: Performs adaptive optimization
    Return OptimizationAction 

Note: Predictive Memory Management
Type called "MemoryPredictor":
    model as MLModel
    prediction_window as Integer
    confidence_threshold as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "MemoryPrediction":
    estimated_allocations as Integer
    estimated_deallocations as Integer
    recommended_gc_trigger as String
    confidence as Float
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "predict_memory_needs" that takes predictor as MemoryPredictor and current_state as MemoryState returns MemoryPrediction:
    Let features be extract_features(current_state)
    Let prediction be predictor.model.predict(features)
    If prediction.confidence is greater than predictor.confidence_threshold:
        Return MemoryPrediction with:
            estimated_allocations as prediction.allocations
            estimated_deallocations as prediction.deallocations
            recommended_gc_trigger as prediction.gc_timing
            confidence as prediction.confidence
            metadata as dictionary containing
    Return None

Process called "adaptive_gc_schedule" that takes gc as GCAlgorithm and predictor as MemoryPredictor returns None:
    Let prediction be predict_memory_needs(predictor, get_current_memory_state())
    If prediction is not None:
        If prediction.recommended_gc_trigger is "now":
            gc_collect(gc)
        Otherwise:
            schedule_gc_at(gc, prediction.recommended_gc_trigger)
    Return None

Process called "ai_memory_feedback" that takes predictor as MemoryPredictor and stats as MemoryStats returns FeedbackReport:
    Note: Provides real-time feedback and optimization suggestions
    Let prediction be predict_memory_needs(predictor, stats)
    Return FeedbackReport with:
        prediction as prediction
        suggestions as generate_optimization_suggestions(prediction)
        metadata as dictionary containing 